### Login as Admin / Asset Manager to authenticate
POST http://localhost:5000/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "admin@assetflow.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

###

### 1. ASSET ALLOCATIONS
### Get all allocations
GET http://localhost:5000/api/allocations?page=1&limit=10

### Allocate an Asset (Use actual assetId and userId)
POST http://localhost:5000/api/allocations
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "assetId": "{{assetId}}",
  "userId": "{{userId}}",
  "expectedReturnDate": "2026-12-31T23:59:59Z"
}

### Return an Asset (Replace :id with assetId)
POST http://localhost:5000/api/allocations/{{assetId}}/return
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "returnCondition": "GOOD",
  "returnRemarks": "Returned in normal working condition"
}

###

### 2. RESOURCE BOOKINGS
### Get all bookings
GET http://localhost:5000/api/bookings?page=1&limit=10

### Book a Resource (e.g. Conference Room or Vehicle - Use bookable assetId)
POST http://localhost:5000/api/bookings
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "assetId": "{{bookableAssetId}}",
  "startTime": "2026-08-15T10:00:00Z",
  "endTime": "2026-08-15T12:00:00Z",
  "purpose": "Monthly review meeting"
}

### Cancel a Booking (Replace :id with bookingId)
POST http://localhost:5000/api/bookings/{{bookingId}}/cancel
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "cancellationReason": "Meeting rescheduled"
}

###

### 3. MAINTENANCE REQUESTS
### Get all maintenance requests
GET http://localhost:5000/api/maintenance?page=1&limit=10

### Raise a Maintenance Request (Any user can report fault)
POST http://localhost:5000/api/maintenance
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "assetId": "{{assetId}}",
  "title": "Screen flickering",
  "description": "The laptop monitor started flickering frequently after update",
  "priority": "MEDIUM"
}

### Assign Technician (Replace :id with requestId - Manager/Admin only)
PATCH http://localhost:5000/api/maintenance/{{requestId}}/assign
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "assignedToId": "{{technicianId}}"
}

### Resolve Maintenance Request (Replace :id with requestId)
PATCH http://localhost:5000/api/maintenance/{{requestId}}/resolve
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "resolutionNotes": "Replaced the display cable. Screen tested okay.",
  "afterPhotoUrl": ""
}

###

### 4. TRANSFER REQUESTS
### Get all transfer requests
GET http://localhost:5000/api/transfers?page=1&limit=10

### Create a Transfer Request (Must be an allocated asset)
POST http://localhost:5000/api/transfers
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "assetId": "{{allocatedAssetId}}",
  "toUserId": "{{targetUserId}}",
  "reason": "Developer moving to QA team"
}

### Approve or Reject a Transfer (Replace :id with transferId - Manager/Admin only)
POST http://localhost:5000/api/transfers/{{transferId}}/action
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "action": "APPROVE",
  "remarks": "Approved and updated department records"
}
